      {
        "id": 4043840,
        "name": "J@son Tr@ughber",
        "username": "Jason_T",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jason_t/{size}/2319_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-04-01T12:12:18.216Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Good to hear William\u2019s wines are doing well.  They sound lovely.  Thanks for the read on the \u201821 vintage as well.</p>\n<p>I\u2019ve yet to taste any so far and it\u2019s been hard to make heads or tails of what\u2019s written.  A lot of talk about \u201821 being a bad / off vintage with thin wines.  But then the consensus view from those I follow seems to be that this is no doubt a lighter vintage, but more classically styled, and still quite good.  Seems your notes are more aligned with that view.  If that\u2019s the case, these sound like wines I\u2019ll enjoy.</p>",
