      {
        "id": 4043881,
        "name": "Greg Kahn",
        "username": "Greg_K",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/ecccb3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2023-04-01T13:56:00.972Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Chet, you are far more diligent than I on notes and are putting me to shame!</p>\n<p>This was my second time tasting the Aligote in barrel, and I really love the way it\u2019s evolving. It\u2019s a wonderful expression of the grape, and the oak choice is quite apt!  I particularly enjoyed the Etelois of the 3 reds (all of which I thought were excellent), though obviously it\u2019s still quite early in the development for either of the 3. Also, after 4 visits earlier in the day and a very young Chambolle at lunch, it was the most welcoming, I think, which may have colored my perceptions.</p>",
